===============
  Fingertier
===============

Fingertier (German for the Aye-eye) is a minimalistic finger friendly music 
player for mobile devices. It is optimised for smart phones with small touch 
screens, like the OpenMoko Freerunner.

-----------------
Dependencies:
-----------------
 * Vala > 0.7.0
 * GLib-2.0
 * GTK+2.0
 * GIO-2.0
 * Gstreamer-0.10

-----------------
Build:
-----------------
 type 'make'

-----------------
Run:
-----------------
 type 'make test'

-----------------
Configuration:
-----------------
 Edit 'LIBRARY_PATH' in ~/.fingertier/fingertier.conf to setup your music 
 library folder.
 Files called 'cover.jpg' are displayed by the player.

-----------------
Packaging opkg:
-----------------
You need a working OpenMoko toolchain.
Help: http://wiki.openmoko.org/wiki/Toolchain

Install the dependencies:
toolchain: opkg-target install gstreamer-0.10-dev gio-2.0-dev gtk+-2.0-dev glib-2.0-dev
on the moko: opkg install gstreamer-0.10 gio-2.0 gtk+-2.0 glib-2.0-dev

Extract fingertier into a folder 'fingertier'.
Run: om-make-ipkg fingertier

Copy the package on your Moko, install and run it:
scp fingertier_0.1_armv4t.ipk root@192.168.0.202:
ssh root@192.168.0.202 opkg install fingertier_0.1_armv4t.ipk
ssh root@192.168.0.202 DISPLAY=:0.0 fingertier



